  "texts": [
    "The vanilla transformer architecture was designed for sequence-to-sequence modelling and was comprised of encoder-decoder blocks.",
    "Since then, alternative transformer architectures have been designed for different NLP tasks.",
    "These are encoder-only transformers such as BERT (Devlin et al., 2019), used for natural language understanding and decoder-only transformers such as the GPT family (Radford et al., 2018), utilised for sequence generation.",
    "However, differences between these architectures are not crucial for the goal of this section.1 3",
    "All of the highlights, textual clues, and abductive inferences were provided by human annotators during the creation of the dataset.1 3"
  ],
